Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a theory for agile governance, which involves the use of IT and effective governance to deliver value to the business. This topic is closely related to software engineering (cs.SE) and cybernetics (cs.CY), as well as computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) which are likely to be relevant in the context of agile governance. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the interaction between different constructs and factors in the context of organizational performance and business competitiveness.
